article.headline: Arkansas St. 55, Murray St. 47
article.story: JONESBORO, Ark. -- Donald Boone and Shawn Morgan scored a total of 31 points and grabbed 13 rebounds between them Wednesday night as Arkansas State beat Murray State 55-47. Murray State (1-1) led 28-23 at the half after hitting 48 percent of its shots from the field. But in the second half, the percentage of shots made by the Racers fell to 27 percent, and they fell quickly behind. Meanwhile, Arkansas State improved its shooting percentage from 27 percent in the first half to 48 percent after intermission. Boone finished with 16 points and Morgan had 15. Morgan also grabbed 8 rebounds, while Boone had 5. Danero Thomas led Murray State with 16 points, while Ivan Aska added 13. ASU (2-1) is without forward Yima Chia-Kur until mid-January because of an NCAA ruling.
